### User:
How do you align a row of divs to the right using flex in css?  Show me an example.

### Response:


Here is an example of how to align a row of div elements to the right using Flexbox in CSS:
```css
div {
    display: flex;
}

div > * {
    margin-right: 10px;
}
```
This code will create a container `div` element with all child elements displayed as inline blocks. The `display: flex;` property is used to enable Flexbox behavior on the parent div, and the `margin-right:` property is applied to each child element to space them out evenly along the right edge of their parent.

You can see this in action here: https://jsfiddle.net/m1L7jnqe/.
